  "definition": {
    "en": "Calcitonin Salmon is synthetic salmon calcitonin, and is a peptide consisting of 32 amino acid residues. It contains not less than 4000 Units of calcitonin salmon per 1 mg of peptide."
  },
  "appearance": {
    "en": "Calcitonin Salmon occurs as a white powder. It is freely soluble in water. It dissolves in dilute acetic acid. Dissolve 20 mg of Calcitonin Salmon in 2 mL of water: the pH of the solution is between 5.0 and 7.0. It is hygroscopic."
  },
